    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Seven of thirteen credibility factors were assessed and all meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors were not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scoping guidance. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to support the regulatory decision that RH < 1 under worst-case operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The assessment team accepted the package on the basis of quantitative validation evidence across five operating points and demonstrated mesh convergence. Use error was noted as not-assessed; the team concluded this was acceptable given MRL 2 requirements, without further evaluation of clinical deployment human-factors conditions.",
